This study develops and uses a new ﬂuorescent false neurotransmitter,
FFN200, which is taken up into vesicles via VMAT2. While most dopamine
terminals exhibit depolarization induced Ca2+ entry, only 20% of them
release FFN200 in response to action potentials, indicating that many
dopamine varicosities are silent.
