This study examines dopamine levels in the nucleus accumbens and
somatic dopamine neuron ﬁring in the ventral tegmental area during
reward-driven learning. Remarkably, striatal dopamine increases during
motivation without an increase in somatic ﬁring, indicating that extra-
cellular dopamine is regulated independent of somatic ﬁring.
