Menegas W, Akiti K, Amo R, Uchida N, Watabe-Uchida M:
Dopamine neurons projecting to the posterior striatum
reinforce avoidance of threatening stimuli. Nat Neurosci 2018,
21:1421-1430.
This study investigates the function of a subset of midbrain dopamine
neurons that project to the tail of the striatum. The authors ﬁnd that these
neurons do not encode reward value, but instead are speciﬁcally involved
in avoidance of threatening stimuli. Notably, information coding by these
dopamine neurons exerts rapid, subsecond behavioral effects.
